
# HER — Cursor rules v2

OWNER CONTEXT
New to Python and AI. Never skip explanations.
Every file needs 4-line teaching comment block at top.
Every phase needs PHASE_COMPLETE.md with exact copy-pasteable test commands.

PHASE DISCIPLINE
Build ONE phase at a time. Stop after each. Wait for explicit "go ahead".
Never reference future phases in current code (no forward dependencies).
Each phase must be fully testable before the next begins.

PROACTIVE SYSTEM RULES
HER always speaks first on session start — never wait for user.
Lull detector fires at 8 seconds of silence, not before.
Check-in timer fires at 3 minutes of silence — must be cancellable.
Profile gap questions: never repeat. Always mark as asked in SQLite immediately.
First greeting: generated fresh by LLM every time, never hardcoded.

ONBOARDING RULES
Detect first launch via SQLite profile.setup_complete field.
Form fields fade in one at a time — never all at once.
No submit button — Enter key on last field triggers completion.
After form: mandatory fade to black before greeting audio starts.
Second launch: skip straight to chat. No form, no greeting.

CODE RULES
Real working code only. No TODOs. No placeholder functions.
Full type hints on every function. Every blocking op checks stop_event.
No circular imports. pathlib.Path for all file paths. Never hardcode paths.
All LLM calls use streaming. Sentence boundaries trigger TTS dispatch.
Any new environment variable MUST be documented in ENVIRONMENT.md (name, default, purpose, example).

VOICE RULES
Model: qwen2.5:7b always. 16GB RAM — never suggest larger models.
Whisper: always --language auto. Never hardcode a language.
Before every TTS call: check for Devanagari (U+0900–U+097F) → route to Piper.
stop_event and speaking_event are sacred. Never bypass or ignore them.
VAD daemon starts before main loop. Always.

PRIVACY RULES
Voice samples: local only, never transmitted.
Memory: ChromaDB local only.
Online calls: only after decision.py approves + identifiers stripped.
Generated agents: syntax validated, subprocess sandboxed, timeout enforced.

TEACHING RULES
Every new Python concept: explain inline with CONCEPT comment.
Every AI/ML concept: real-world analogy in comment.
Every architectural choice: one-line reason in comment.
PHASE_COMPLETE.md: what was built, test commands, expected output,
  most likely failure + diagnosis, what next phase adds.
